The Northern Oasis is the administrative gateway to the eastern desert. Caravans first encounter law, quotas, and witness-seals here.
Local saying: "South drinks, north counts."

Fed by the weakest fracture of the Deepwell Confluence. Low volume, high mineral content, seasonally variable.
Water is potable but brackish. There are no garden terraces, fountains, or ceremonial pools.

The Reedline Wardens, a military-administrative water audit corps, enforce allocation with measured precision.
They ration by measurement and have accumulated governing authority through control of the survival resource.
Their oath-bowls and witness seals are accepted across the entire oasis network.

The Survey Cairn Ring preserves Keeper-era directional-distance glyphs in weathered but readable form.
Cairn Brokers authenticate cargo and maintain Trust Ledgers tracking caravan reliability.

The oasis hardened further after the Ninth Meridian catastrophe.
It drew a lesson from the Great Oasis's broken Compact: measure precisely enough that no one can take more than you can spare.
